title: Presidential Election
subtitle: Holt runs for re-election...
view-if: year = 2077 and (month = 7 or month = 8)
frequency: 1000
max-visits: 1
new-page: true
on-arrival: rovich_campaign = 0; richter_campaign = 0; bauer_support_holt = 0; presidential_election_seen = 1; nsnawp_candidate = "Bauer" if bauer_deported == 0 else nsnawp_candidate = "Göring";
tags: event
go-to: election_algorithm
set-jump: pres_election
face-image: img/holt_election.jpg

@pres_election

The presidential election is coming up soon. [? if ip_in_government = 0 : While the position of Chancellor is typically more important, recent governments have depended on the president's emergency decree powers, making the office vital. ?] [? if bauer_deported==0 : The Nazis will run Bauer, while the NCWPP will run Petrov. A victory for Bauer would mean the end of parliamentary democracy, and the beginning of an era of unspeakable horrors. ?][? if bauer_deported==1 : Since Bauer has been deported, the Nazis will run Hermann Göring in his stead. He is widely seen as a proxy for Bauer, who, despite his legal persecution, retains a popular base who wishes to see him returned to Germany. Meanwhile, the NCWPP will run Ivan Petrov. ?]
[? if sapd_formed: The SAPD, our former leftists, are supporting Petrov of the NCWPP, and will likely share an endorsement with the Communists. ?]

# if bauer is deported, who would nsnawp run? Duesterberg? or Goering?
# Goering runs, essentially as a proxy for Bauer, who is now stateless.

Many are calling for us to support the incumbent emergency mayor Holt, despite his well-known reactionary tendencies. Is he truly the best bulwark against Bauer's ascension? On the other hand, many in our party are calling for Rovich or Richter to run.

[? if cp_relation >= 50 : Another strange possibilty is an united front with the Communists, either to support Petrov or our own candidate. ?]


- @support_holt: Support Welton Holt of the DP.
- @support_rovich: Run Misha Rovich of the IPNC.
- @support_richter: Run Johnathan Richter of the IPNC                                              
- @support_petrov: Support Ivan Petrov of the NCWPP.

@support_holt
subtitle: This is the default option.

Despite his known reactionary nature, Holt has at least been keeping the Nazis at bay. Thus, we must support him.

- @final_election: The final vote...

@support_rovich
subtitle: This will cost us 2 resources.
choose-if: resources >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 2; rovich_campaign = 1
go-to: rovich_campaign

It takes effort to run a somewhat unexpected campaign. First, Rovich has to be convinced to run. He himself had supported voting for Holt, and it takes a good deal of prodding to convince him of his destiny.

@support_richter
choose-if: 1 == 2
unavailable-subtitle: In his sickly state, he cannot be expected to run.
                                              
@support_petrov
choose-if: cp_relation >= 50 and reformist_strength < left_strength
unavailable-subtitle: [? if cp_relation < 50 : We do not have good enough relations with the Communists, so they are not even willing to accept our support. ?] [? if liberal_strength >= socialist_strength : The libertarians are able to dissuade the party from supporting this arrangement. ?]

Supporting Petrov is rather unpopular in our party, even if the Communists accept our support. Are we sure?

- @support_petrov_2: Yes, we will support Petrov, despite the libertarians' pleas against it.
- @support_rovich: Support Rovich instead.
- @support_holt: Support Holt instead.

@support_petrov_2
on-arrival: ip_support_petrov = 1; reformist_dissent += 15; Federalists_dissent += 10; labor_dissent += 5; neorevisionist_dissent += 10; catholics_ip -= 5; workers_ip -= 3; cp_relation += 10; communist_coalition += 2; fp_relation -= 15; lp_relation -= 15; ddp_relation -= 10

Fine. We have thrown our support to Chairman Petrov of the NCWPP.

- @final_election: The final vote...

@rovich_campaign

- @convince_fp: Convince the Federalist Party.
- @convince_cp: Convince the Communists.
- @convince_libertarians: Convince the remaining libertarians, wherever they are.
- @final_election: The final vote...

@convince_fp
choose-if: ip_votes >= fp_votes
unavailable-subtitle: The Federalists knows that they are more popular than us; they do not see a reason to support our candidate.
on-arrival: {!
Q.fp_support_rovich = 0;
if (Q.fp_relation >= 55 || (Q.fp_relation > 35 && Q.fp_party_leader == "Joos")) {
    Q.fp_support_rovich = 1;
} else if (Q.fp_relation <= 35) {
    Q.fp_support_rovich = 0;
} else {
    Q.fp_support_rovich = 2;
}
!}
go-to: fp_failed if fp_support_rovich = 0 or (fp_support_rovich == 2 and historical_mode); fp_success if fp_support_rovich = 1; fp_partial if fp_support_rovich = 2 and not historical_mode
max-visits: 1

We remind the Federalists leaders of Holt's anti-Catholicism, and try to convince them that Holt's path will eventually lead to Bauer. We also remind them of the successes they've had as part of the Weimar coalition in Prussia with Otto Rovich, and our support for the Federalists candidate Wilhelm Marx in the 1925 presidential election.

@fp_success
go-to: rovich_campaign

The Federalists are convinced! They will be part of the Rovich coalition.

@fp_partial

The Federalists are not satisfied with our arguments, but they are open to being convinced. They are willing to run a joint campaign if we front the resources.

- @pay_fp: Give them the resources they need.
- @rovich_campaign: Forget about the Federalists.

@pay_fp
choose-if: resources >= 3
subtitle: -3 resources
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources (need 3)
on-arrival: resources -= 3; fp_support_rovich = 1
go-to: rovich_campaign

With our resources, the Federalists are convinced to support Rovich over Holt.

@fp_failed
go-to: rovich_campaign

Unfortunately, we fail to turn them away from Holt.

@convince_cp
choose-if: ip_votes >= cp_votes
unavailable-subtitle: The NCWPP knows that they are more popular than us; they do not see a reason to support our candidate.
max-visits: 1

The NCWPP is supporting their own candidate, Ivan Petrov. [? if cp_relation >= 50 : However, they are willing to be convinced to drop their campaign and support Rovich; how do we convince them? ?][? if cp_relation < 50 or cp_party_leader != "Conciliators" : They do not seem willing to be convinced. ?]

- @cp_resources: Use our resources.
- @cp_relations: Use our good relations.
- @rovich_campaign: Forget about the NCWPP.

@cp_resources
view-if: cp_relation >= 50 and not historical_mode
choose-if: resources >= 3
subtitle: -3 resources
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources (need 3).
on-arrival: resources -= 3; cp_support_rovich = 1
go-to: rovich_campaign

The NCWPP now endorses Rovich in the presidential election! We ask them to keep their support low-key, so as to not alienate the bourgeois voters.

@cp_relations
view-if: cp_relation >= 60 or (cp_party_leader == "Conciliators" and cp_relation >= 45)
unavailable-subtitle: Our relations are not good enough.
on-arrival: cp_support_rovich = 1
go-to: rovich_campaign

The NCWPP now endorses Rovich in the presidential election! We ask them to keep their support low-key, so as to not alienate the bourgeois voters.

@convince_libertarians
max-visits: 1
go-to: convince_libertarians_success if lp_relation >= 50; convince_libertarians_fail if lp_relation < 50

The libertarian vote is relatively miniscule, so they will probably be of minimal help to us. For what it's worth, they *do* have major support among nomads.

@convince_libertarians_success
on-arrival: lp_support_rovich = 1
go-to: rovich_campaign

Thanks to our good relations, the LPNC has promised to support Rovich in the election.

@convince_libertarians_fail
on-arrival: lp_support_rovich = 0
go-to: rovich_campaign

We failed to convince the LPNC to support Rovich.



@final_election
on-arrival: election_round = 0
go-to: election_algorithm
set-jump: post_election


@post_election
on-arrival: {!
Q.rovich_votes = 0;
Q.holt_votes = 0;
Q.bauer_votes = 0;
Q.petrov_votes = 0;

// initial phase:
Q.bauer_votes += Q.nsnawp_normalized;

if (Q.rovich_campaign) {
    Q.rovich_votes += Q.ip_normalized;
    Q.rovich_votes += Q.ddp_normalized;
    if (Q.fp_support_rovich && Q.fp_support_rovich == 1) {
        Q.rovich_votes += Q.fp_normalized;
    } else {
        Q.holt_votes += Q.fp_normalized;
    }
    if (Q.cp_support_rovich) {
        Q.rovich_votes += Q.cp_normalized;
        if (Q.sapd_formed && Q.sapd_votes) {
            Q.rovich_votes += Q.sapd_normalized;
        }
    } else {
        Q.petrov_votes += Q.cp_normalized;
        if (Q.sapd_formed && Q.sapd_votes) {
            Q.petrov_votes += Q.sapd_normalized;
        }
    }
    if (Q.lp_support_rovich) {
        Q.rovich_votes += Q.lp_normalized;
    } else {
        Q.holt_votes += Q.lp_normalized;
    }
} else if (Q.ip_support_petrov) {
    Q.petrov_votes += Q.cp_normalized;
    Q.petrov_votes += Q.ip_normalized;
    Q.holt_votes += Q.fp_normalized;
    Q.holt_votes += Q.ddp_normalized;
    Q.holt_votes += Q.lp_normalized;
} else {
    Q.holt_votes += Q.ip_normalized;
    Q.holt_votes += Q.fp_normalized;
    Q.holt_votes += Q.ddp_normalized;
    Q.holt_votes += Q.lp_normalized;
    Q.petrov_votes += Q.cp_normalized;
}
if (Q.bauer_support_holt) {
    Q.bauer_votes -= Q.nsnawp_normalized;
    Q.holt_votes += Q.nsnawp_normalized;
}

if (Q.holt_to_rovich_bonus) {
    Q.holt_votes -= Q.holt_to_rovich_bonus;
    Q.rovich_votes += Q.holt_to_rovich_bonus;
}
if (Q.petrov_to_rovich_bonus) {
    Q.petrov_votes -= Q.petrov_to_rovich_bonus;
    Q.rovich_votes += Q.petrov_to_rovich_bonus;
}

// check for majority
Q.holt_votes = Math.round(Q.holt_votes*1000)/10;
Q.rovich_votes = Math.round(Q.rovich_votes*1000)/10;
Q.bauer_votes = Math.round(Q.bauer_votes*1000)/10;
Q.petrov_votes = Math.round(Q.petrov_votes*1000)/10;

Q.holt_majority = (Q.holt_votes >= 50);
Q.petrov_majority = (Q.petrov_votes >= 50);
Q.bauer_majority = (Q.bauer_votes >= 50);
Q.rovich_majority = (Q.rovich_votes >= 50);
Q.any_majority = Q.holt_majority | Q.petrov_majority | Q.bauer_majority | Q.rovich_majority;

// check for plurality
Q.holt_plurality = (Q.holt_votes >= Q.bauer_votes && Q.holt_votes >= Q.rovich_votes && Q.holt_votes >= Q.petrov_votes);
Q.petrov_plurality = (Q.petrov_votes >= Q.holt_votes && Q.petrov_votes >= Q.rovich_votes && Q.petrov_votes >= Q.bauer_votes);
Q.bauer_plurality = (Q.bauer_votes >= Q.holt_votes && Q.bauer_votes >= Q.rovich_votes && Q.bauer_votes >= Q.petrov_votes);
Q.rovich_plurality = (Q.rovich_votes >= Q.holt_votes && Q.rovich_votes >= Q.bauer_votes && Q.rovich_votes >= Q.petrov_votes);
// If no candidate gets above 50%, then there's a second round. In the second round, a plurality wins. 
Q.election_round += 1;

// making the vote numbers nicer for the display
Q.holt_votes_disp = Q.holt_votes.toFixed(1);
Q.rovich_votes_disp = Q.rovich_votes.toFixed(1);
Q.bauer_votes_disp = Q.bauer_votes.toFixed(1);
Q.petrov_votes_disp = Q.petrov_votes.toFixed(1);
!}
go-to: holt_wins if holt_majority == 1; petrov_wins if petrov_majority == 1; bauer_wins if bauer_majority == 1; rovich_wins if rovich_majority == 1; no_majority_round1 if any_majority == 0 and election_round == 1; round2_results if election_round >= 2

Results:

Holt - [+ holt_votes_disp +]%

[+ nsnawp_candidate +] - [+ bauer_votes_disp +]%

[? if cp_support_rovich == 0 : Petrov - [+ petrov_votes_disp +]% ?]

[? if rovich_campaign > 0 : Rovich - [+ rovich_votes_disp +]% ?]

@no_majority_round1
on-arrival: bauer_support_holt = 1 if (rovich_plurality or petrov_plurality)
go-to: round2_menu

There is no majority in this round. In the second round, any candidate who wins a plurality will win overall. What should we do?

[? if rovich_plurality or petrov_plurality : In order to consolidate the vote for the Right, and to prevent a socialist from becoming president, [+ nsnawp_candidate +] is no longer running in the second round, and has switched his endorsement to Holt. ?]


@round2_menu

- @round2_convince_fp: Convince the Federalists to switch their support to us.
- @round2_convince_cp: Convince the NCWPP to switch their support to us. 
- @round2_holt: Switch our support to Holt.
- @round2_petrov: Switch our support to Petrov of the NCWPP.
- @round2_vote: Let the second round voting begin.


@round2_convince_fp
view-if: rovich_campaign > 0 and fp_support_rovich != 1 
choose-if: ip_votes >= fp_votes
unavailable-subtitle: The Federalists know that they are more popular than us; they do not see a reason to support our candidate.
on-arrival: {!
Q.fp_support_rovich = 0;
// if Holt support is greater than Bauer and Rovich support, this should be much harder

if ((Q.fp_relation >= 55 && Q.rovich_votes >= Q.holt_votes) || (Q.fp_relation > 35 && Q.fp_party_leader == "Joos")) {
    Q.fp_support_rovich = 1;
    if (Q.bauer_support_holt) {
        Q.holt_to_rovich_bonus += Q.other_normalized/2;
    }
} else if (Q.fp_relation >= 50 && Q.bauer_support_holt) {
    Q.fp_support_rovich = 1;
    Q.holt_to_rovich_bonus += Q.other_normalized/2;
} else if (Q.fp_relation <= 35 || (Q.fp_relation <= 45 && Q.rovich_votes < Q.holt_votes && Q.holt_votes > Q.bauer_votes && Q.difficulty >= 0)) {
    Q.fp_support_rovich = 0;
} else {
    Q.fp_support_rovich = 2;
}
!}
go-to: r2_fp_failed if fp_support_rovich = 0 or (fp_support_rovich = 2 and historical_mode); r2_fp_success if fp_support_rovich = 1; r2_fp_partial if fp_support_rovich = 2 and not historical_mode
max-visits: 1

@r2_fp_success
go-to: round2_menu
on-departure: bauer_support_holt = 1 if rovich_votes + fp_votes > bauer_votes

[? if bauer_support_holt : The Federalists's opinion is affected by the Nazis' support of Holt, and is willing to turn away from him. ?] The Federalists are convinced! They will be part of the Rovich coalition. [? if bauer_support_holt : In addition, they will also bring in some minor parties who will support us. ?]

[? if not bauer_support_holt and rovich_votes + fp_votes > bauer_votes: With the Federalist Party supporting Rovich, [+ nsnawp_candidate +] has dropped out of the race, and the Nazis have endorsed Holt to prevent a socialist from becoming president. ?]

@r2_fp_partial

The Federalists are not satisfied with our arguments, but they are open to being convinced[? if bauer_support_holt: , especially given the Nazis' support for Holt. ?]. They are willing to run a joint campaign if we front the resources.

- @r2_pay_fp: Give them the resources they need.
- @round2_menu: Forget about the Federalists.

@r2_pay_fp
choose-if: resources >= 2
subtitle: -2 resources
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources (need 2)
on-arrival: resources -= 2; fp_support_rovich = 1
on-departure: bauer_support_holt = 1 if rovich_votes + fp_votes > bauer_votes
go-to: round2_menu

With our resources, the Federalists are convinced to support Rovich over Holt.

[? if not bauer_support_holt and rovich_votes + fp_votes > bauer_votes: With the Federalist Party supporting Rovich, [+ nsnawp_candidate +] has dropped out of the race, and the Nazis have endorsed Holt to prevent a socialist from becoming president. ?]

@r2_fp_failed
go-to: round2_menu

Unfortunately, we fail to turn them away from Holt. [? if holt_votes > rovich_votes : Given that Holt received more votes than Rovich, they believe that we should turn to Holt, not the other way around. ?]




@round2_convince_cp
